  "text": "2.3.1 Overview of the Random Subset Assignment Scheme. We choose the random subset assignment scheme because it can be considered as a generalization of several key predistribution schemes. Indeed, the basic probabilistic key predistribution scheme [CITATION_1] ] is a special case of the random subset assignment scheme when each key is considered as a 0-degree polynomial [CITATION_2] . Moreover, the key predistribution scheme in [CITATION_3] is essentially equivalent to the random subset assignment scheme in [CITATION_4] . Since most key predistribution schemes (except for the random pairwise keys scheme [CITATION_5] ) are based on the random and independent distribution of key units to sensor nodes, the results obtained through improving the random subset assignment scheme can be easily generalized to those schemes.",
